node.text:
Affirmation of the Day: I am releasing any expectations, thoughts, beliefs, patterns and behaviors that no longer serve my highest good and potential. I will not mistake my valuable time of spiritual solitude for loneliness. I give myself grace and compassion as I move forward through my healing journey. I am so powerful, I believe in myself, I am so proud of my abilities. 🧡
featured work: from “flowers on the moon” by @iambrillyant

node.text:
Affirmation of the Day: I am proud of myself for how far I’ve come. I am powerful beyond measure. I am filled with love and gratitude. I know who I am. I let go of old limitations and beliefs, self-sabotaging behaviors, and I lean into an empowering self-narrative instead. I let go, and I am at peace. 🧡
#healing #affirmations

node.text: Affirmation of the Day: I won't stop going, even if I'm the only one who believes in my dreams. In my moments of feeling lack and doubt, I will change the story I tell myself. I know my mind is full of brilliant ideas that have the power to benefit myself and others. Every challenge, every loss, and every success is a learning lesson that brings me closer to my goals. I got this. 🧡 Which reminders are resonating with you today?

node.text: Affirmation of the Day: I am not in control of others, how they think, how they feel, what they do - and that is okay. I release the need to be. I am, however, in control of my life, my proximity to what doesn’t align with my values, and my perspective. It’s good to feel good. I am worthy. I am on my way. 🧡
